Title: Converting floats to strings quickly
Description: When serializing data to JSON, CSV or when logging, we convert numbers to strings. Floating-point numbers are stored in binary, but we need them as decimal strings. The first formally published algorithm is Steele and White's Dragon schemes (specifically Dragin2) in 1990.
